CREATED BY: PIYUSH MAHAJAN


Problem Statement

You have a dataset related to characteristics of Beans like their Area, Perimeter, Roundness etc. Given that you have to build Machine learning model that can predict the class or category of bean

Dataset Description

The dataset folder contains the following files:

  1. training dataset contained in train.csv file
  2. Testing dataset contained in test.csv file

2.2  Duplicate Values    ⤒

Let's Check is there any duplicate values exist or not

  NOTE:

- How to Handle duplicates is completely in the hands of Data Scientist or Machine learning engineer.
- You can drop them or Just keep them, Both have their Advantage and Dis-advantages
- If There are Duplicates in the training set, it results in increasing the sample weight of those cases. In That case, Removal of true duplicates will be a good thing.
- But There are scenarios where duplicated data has meaning and in that case we keeps the duplicates In Given Dataset, I am going to keep the duplicates. Because The dataset is about characteristics of Beans and there are chances that two beans may have exact same characteristics, but still they are two different Beans. So i am going to keep them, Still i will decide this during countplots.

2.4  Pie chart    ⤒

In [ ]:
def Pie_plots(data_frame, feature_name):
    label = data_frame[feature_name].value_counts().index
    values = data_frame[feature_name].value_counts().values
    fig = go.Figure(data=[go.Pie(labels=label, values = values,
         hole=0.3, pull = [0.025]*len(label),
         )])
    fig.show()
In [ ]:
Pie_plots(train_df, 'Class')

3.  MODEL BUILDING    ⤒

  APPROACH

- For model building, I am going to use two types of dataset 1. Whole dataset and 2. Selecting K-best Features
- The dataset is going to be splitted into two parts one for training and other for validation purpose and we already have separate dataset for testing.
- For starting I am going to use logistic Regression model, because of its simplicity and easy to use. After that if logistic model failed to give good accuracy and other metrics, Then I will try different models
- I am going to use Feature Transformation, because all feature have different range and units, so i am going to use MinMax Scaler.

3.8  CONCLUSION    ⤒

  RESULT

- We have tried two models 1. Logistic Regression and 2. XGBoost model. Both models are providing best accuracies and F1 scores but they is a small difference in speed and accuracy
- Logistic Model accuracy is lower compare to XGBoost, but it is fast and simple
- XGBoost model accuracy is good as compare to Logistic Model, but it is slower because of Ensembling.
From These two models I am going to use XGBoost model as final model, because of its performance and there is very small difference between their speeds which i am going to ignore.
